      "message": "DISABLED_TEST() is for tests that can only be disabled dynamically at runtime.\n\nAs an x86-only feature, DAZ is something that we know we won’t be supporting when we’re building for non-x86 at compile time. Not to mention, CPUX86Anything() won’t work on non-x86. This is not a runtime matter.\n\nThe correct way to handle this situation is to just #if out the entire TEST_F under the desired condition.\n\nNote that the correct condition to test for is not defined(ARCH_CPU_ARM64), but actually !defined(ARCH_CPU_X86_FAMILY).",
